# --- workspaces/ (two audiences — IMP-212) ---
# MAINTAINER-SCOPE default: this is the PUBLIC framework repo, which must never
# ship real or test client data, so project workspaces are ignored here. Only the
# _template scaffold (no client data) is versioned. Every workspace /init creates
# carries its OWN .gitignore (governing what is versionable INSIDE it), which YOU
# control in your own repo.
#
# Using Ignite in your OWN (typically private) project repo? Your matured
# workspace IS the versionable source of truth (see AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md). To
# version it and collaborate over GitHub, un-ignore your project by adding, per
# project, BELOW these lines:
#     !workspaces/<YOUR_PROJECT_ID>/
# that project's own workspaces/<ID>/.gitignore then keeps memory indexes and
# generated HTML out. Do not delete the blanket rule wholesale in a fork you push
# publicly.
workspaces/*
!workspaces/.gitkeep
!workspaces/_template/
!workspaces/_template/**
# Archives and local tooling residue must never be committed (IMP-003)
*.7z
*.zip
.sentinel_doctor_write_test
# Portfolio dashboard + per-artifact HTML views: regenerable and may embed client
# content, so ignored repo-wide as a maintainer-safe default (workspace-scoped
# copies also live in workspaces/_template/.gitignore for un-ignored projects).
dashboard.html
**/08_context_packs/views/*.html
# Local evolution/operational memory: not published to the public repo
docs/
# Maintainer-local agent memory (resume pointers, process notes): never published
CLAUDE.local.md
# Personal handoff documents live outside the repo (IMP-002)
general-proyecto.md
ignite_vnext_final_handoff.md
# Eval run outputs are reproducible; keep reports out of main
tests/evals/reports/
